The paper deals with approximation algorithms for tree spanners, which are a fundamental topic in graph theory and algorithms. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry, combinatorics, and complexity theory. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). Additionally, the paper discusses the NP-completeness of the diameter at most t + 1 tree t-spanner problem, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
